comments:
I'm not sure if this problem is reproducible, as crashes have happened 
throughout the day -- which might have led to a corrupted state.  However, 
this problem should be better handled. 
 
While attempting to compare two files, I got a bogus compare (one half was 
completely empty).  I retried multiple times.  No dice.  Checking the log, I 
found the following exceptions.  I'm not sure whether this is a problem with 
core's caching facility or with team's response to the cache failure.
